reviews_data.review_text: I have tried several things from this bakery and every single one of them were amazing. Also, the people who work there are super nice and it is always spotlessly clean in there. Would definitely recommend. And the fact that they are open till 10 PM is nice.

We visited to get quick brunch and some coffee. The mocha we took was super watery. Wings super oily and cheese sandwich greesy. The menu does not have cost written at the entrance. They'll charge you $$ later. Mocha cost us $7!! And the sandwich and waffle was also really expensive. Not worth it. Disappointed.

Lugar espectacular para tomarte un delicioso postre con cafe, en un ambiente agradable.!  Los pasteles son hermosos y frescos .. ese fue el pastel de mi sobrina quedo sonado para celebrar su primer anito !

What a lovely place. The owner is such a positive loving soul with such great energy. Attentive and sweet. The environment is beautiful, from it's decor to setting and selections, cozy. The food was delicious along with their great selections of desserts.  My family and I look forward to returning.  Thank you all for making it such a wonderful experience.
Los cheesecake y la mejor comida dominicana super recomendados

Wonderful Bakery Cafe!! Delicious Freshly Made Sandwiches!!  Amazing Desserts from all over the world!! Superb Gelato!! We had the Salmon Chipotle, the Chimi Pulled Pork, and the Ground Beef Chop Cheese sandwiches along with fresh brewed coffee and a variety of desserts, everything was out of this world and all served by the extraordinary chef and owner Karina Cooper. This is a must go place and we will be definitely coming back soon :)

I found this bakery on Google after searching for banana pudding because I didn't want to make a whole one myself. La Dolcekca came up & another place but I chose here after seeing people rave about the banana pudding but, I thought it was just ok. I got the biscoff banana pudding. It was good but not worth the drive I took to get there. I also got a tiramisu which was $10 for a small pan & it wasn't sweet at all. Tasted mostly like the coco on top. You can honestly get a bigger slice for less at Publix. I agree with others that say they are overpriced but their price is their price so I won't speak much on that. Overall,  wouldn't go back for the dessert but I didn't have a bad experience. Just a little overhyped per the reviews imo.
The owner was very friendly & inviting - she brewed us fresh coffee and ensured our visit was special.  (The brownie cheesecake is DELICIOUS!)
Friendly atmosphere.... Tres Leches, cupcakes and Empanadas are great! I have a new spot.

The staff was super friendly and the atmosphere is very cute. The choices are almost overwhelming but they talked me through the different options.

I got a strawberry tres leches cake that I think was made really well, I'm just not sure I love tres leches
I go to this spot every weekend and they never disappoint. Amazing pastries and amazing food as-well, just an overall great place to go to eat or enjoy some sweets highly recommend!!
The best bakery in charlotte...
Honestly I have nothing but positive things to say about this establishment. Such vibrant energy every time I walk in
It's too bad that the owner has a nasty attitude full of herself and thinks that she better than everybody!!! I would never ever eat / order from here just because of her nasty attitude

From the pastries to the coffee served on lovely home style grandma dishware to the delectable hot food they serve, dolcecka is amazing! My one complaint is that their prices are exorbitantly high, wouldn't come here as often as I would like because of it. Otherwise it's an adorable cafe and bakery with lots to choose from and very cute funky indoor decor.
AMAZING AMAZING AMAZING!!!!! Visited this place twice today! Food is soooooooo goodddd. If you haven't been this is the place to go.

We came here because this place looked neat on IG. DONT FALL FOR IT. We came in and the entire staff was just scrolling on their phones in the sitting area, and looked at us like we were annoying for showing up. We went to order and the guy behind the counter seemed like he didn't understand the process of placing an order. We ordered our food and an item we ordered was inco.mplete because they didn't have the ingredients. That would be fine but the Lady at the counter agued with us about a refund for an item that they don't have but is on their menu and took our money for when we ordered. The espresso was watery and tasted like cinnamon. They say that have dolce de leches but it is just black coffee with caramel syrup. Every time they asked how the food was and we told them the truth, they proceeded to argue with us about it. Also, I speak Spanish and they didn't know, each time they went back to the kitchen they would talk trash about us in Spanish. I would say skip this place. Also the empanadas were bland and the tables were dirty. Also over priced food

My wife and I walked in for some dessert, this spot seemed appealing as a Dominican New Yorker it's nice to find places that remind you of home. Flan and tres leche was awesome and so was the service.

A cute little family owned cafe bakery hiding in the Woodlawn area. There are so many options here. They also do custom cakes for birthdays and other events.

I had the Turkey Bacon, Egg and Cheese sandwich. Not only did it taste delish, but it was plated so beautifully. The fries was an unexpected but very much appreciated surprise.

No paper places here. Just look at that plating! And look at the spoon that came with my Late! 
(Don't worry, they have To-Go cups and containers.)

Service was quite nice and met expectations. Doing the right thing when things go wrong is very important.

Well done!

This is a hidden and exquisite gem of a place in Charlotte. We've been here twice for coffee and dessert and IT WAS FANTASTIC! The key lime pie is the best I've ever had and the coffee is delicious. My wife has had several different chocolate themed desserts and has raved over how good it was. We live in Virginia and will make it a point to stop here anytime I have business in Charlotte!

WOW!! Visited after a recommendation and WOW! We pretty much had a taste of everything and it's all fantastic! BUT the wings, best in Charlotte, hands down! The owner is super friendly and very attentive! Give this place a try you won't regret it!

Do not get a latte from here. I should have known better when I didn't see an espresso machine or hear them grind any coffee.
I ordered a medium iced half sweet brown sugar cinnamon latte. My husband got a medium iced latte as well. It cost us $17... What I got was sickenly sweet, but also incredibly artificial and watered down. I highly doubt this was actually espresso. My sister got a hot latte and also hated it. I took 2 sips and then threw mine out. Such a waste of money.
Their pastries and food looked really good, and maybe that's what I need to stick to if I come back
Ordered a customize baby shower cake and cupcakes..... everyone was blown away by the taste of everything. She did an amazing job in such an short timeframe

A Perfect Place to Placate your Palate.
First time here. We had an amazing experience! We were greeted warmly at the door, walked through the many menu items, and served graciously and attentively.
Each of our dishes was delightful, my burger, the salmon sandwich and empanadas. Everyone loved them.
Karina has worked every recipe to perfection. The selection while seemingly small, was wide enough for all of us to find something we loved.
Our desserts were scrumptious. We were lucky to get cinnamon rolls straight from the oven, tres leches cake and raspberry sorbet. .
Delicious food (the beef empanadas, Flan and tres leches were amazing) super friendly staff and great atmosphere!
Chimmi sandwich and banana pudding were delicious

First off, we arrived with great excitement to try this new place. It was hit and miss with the various items we tried. The ham & cheese empanada was very good, the seasoning on the beef empanada had too much vinegar and rosemary. The passion fruit flan was good overall, however the tres leches cake was the worst I've ever had and that is simply not okay for a Dominican pastry shop. We tried several other items that were decent overall. Unfortunately, the server forgot to add the rice pudding for our take home order that we paid for, and so sadly we left disappointed with no plans on future repeat business. I guess that's just how it goes sometimes.

LA DOLCEKCA BAKERY CAFE me encanto mucho, la manera confortable que te hace sentir y el ambiente en general muy excelente. Si quieres tener tu Coquette coffee con tus amigas(os) aqui definitivamente sera tu lugar.
I love the pink esthetic on the inside! The salmon chipotle sandwich was to die for! And the biscoff cheesecake was chef's kiss!

My boyfriend and his mom and i came there early today for breakfast. As a New Yorker and Dominican I always love coming here to eat a chopped cheese and pick out a desert. Typically we don't dine in but today when East like Sunday had an hour wait we decided to dine in as his mom has never tried the food. She loved the atmosphere the customer service was lovely and when we asked her about the food 1-10 she gave it a 12. My boyfriend and I love it hear it is a must try the music is giving at your Dominican Tia's house for chisme y cafe ! Not only that she was nice and took out picture making sure the photos came out just right. Everything is so fresh the empanadas, French toast & juice!
The best place in Charlotte, empanadas, chimi and the pastries are to die for!! Must try this family own business!!

This establishment provides an exceptional experience from the moment you step in, greeted with a warm smile. The owner, incredibly kind and welcoming, takes you through a comprehensive tour of the diverse dessert options. If you have a sweet tooth, you'll find an array of tempting treats. For those craving savory snacks, the extensive menu won't disappoint. Whether you opt for a quick pick-up with excellent service or decide to stay, indulging in a meticulously crafted cappuccino adds to the enjoyment. The atmosphere is beautiful and relaxing, making it an all-around fantastic place.

Este establecimiento brinda una experiencia excepcional desde el momento en que entras, recibido con una calida sonrisa. La duena, increiblemente amable y acogedora, te guia a traves de un recorrido completo por las diversas opciones de postres. Si tienes gusto por lo dulce, encontraras una variedad tentadora. Para aquellos que anhelan snacks salados, el extenso menu no te decepcionara. Ya sea que elijas un servicio rapido con atencion excelente o decidas quedarte, y deleitarte con un cappuccino meticulosamente elaborado que se anade a la experiencia. El ambiente es hermoso y relajante, convirtiendolo en un lugar fantastico en todos los aspectos.

The ambience is lovely! The place is very well decorated and full of inspiring quotes. It doesn't feel like a regular coffeeshop, it feels like you are a welcomed guest at an old friend's home. Desserts, coffee, and food are outstanding.

Such a hidden gem! Went in for lunch today and had some amazing sandwiches and empanadas. We ordered the chopped cheese, chimi, and beef and chicken empanadas and they were all outstanding. Staff was super friendly and the interior was fun and definitely eclectic. Can't wait to come back!

Delightful visit. This beautifully decorated space includes cases full of cakes and pastries. We couldn't decide so tried several including a fruit tart bursting with flavor, a chocolate flan, a cheesecake and more. There is a coffee bar and even ice cream! Planning my next visit
5 stars. Great bakery, awesome sandwich and love the home made family vibe here.

As a Puerto Rican/ Dominican woman, I can honestly say this place reminds me of home. Everything is so well seasoned and stuffed. Empanadas, amazing. Chimi, great. But the chopped cheese!! I woke up craving it one morning, placed the order for pick up, got home to eat it and forgot it had mustard in it (I hate mustard)... I cried. I legit cried! My friend called me dramatic until he took a bite and understood why I felt the way I did.

Only con: I wish they would update their website or add a menu on their google page so we know what all is in the sandwiches.

I absolutely loved this place. The owner and her daughter are so attentive. The food is amazing. They make you feel at home! My boyfriend is lactose intolerant and really wanted a hot chocolate and she went about and beyond to prepare him a hot chocolate without milk. I am so happy we found this spot with a "heart & soul" this is going to be my to go spot for coffees and catching up with family and friends!
Delicious pastries, great food and service. Highly recommend!

This bakery is awesome. The food is a bonus to the varieties of cakes and pastries. I've been here several times and always satisfied from everything I've tried. So far, the Chipotle salmon sandwich, Cajun pasta, and burgers are all dope choices. Along with all the empanadas. Go try...
Omg! Absolutely amazing. The environment is sooo homey. The food is delicious. You have to try the chicken empanadas!
Empanada were amazing! The atmosphere was very cute coffee shop vibe. The main course and coffee were also pretty great. Will definitely be back if closer to work would be the new lunch destination

La Dolcekca Bakery Cafe in Charlotte, NC, is a delightful culinary paradox nestled in The Montford Shops, a stone's throw from Angry Ales and Bowlero. It's the kind of place where the Caribbean meets Paris in a New York minute, and you can't help but feel you've stumbled upon a hidden gem.

Upon entry, the sweet serenades of Frank Reyes set the stage for an experience that's as authentically Dominican as it gets, with a French twist. Karina, the owner's daughter and apparent queen of multitasking, greeted me with a smile that could light up the room. The display case was a kaleidoscope of treats - think tres leches in flavors you didn't know existed, flans that wobble just right, and cupcakes that make you question your loyalty to your diet.

Now, let's talk about the menu. It's like the United Nations of pastries and sandwiches. I bravely ventured to try their Chimi, a sandwich that's a culinary hug from the Dominican Republic, squeezed onto what I suspect is French bread. It's a constellation of flavors with pulled pork, tomato, cheese, and a condiment symphony. But wait, there's more - it's pressed to perfection, accompanied by the kind of fries that remind you of childhood and a ramekin of ketchup that's probably just there to feel important.

The price might raise an eyebrow - $15.50 for the Chimi and $8 for the bread pudding - but remember, you're not just buying food; you're funding a culinary dream. However, I must admit, the Chimi was saltier than my last breakup. Next time, I'll stick to the pastries or give their chopped cheese a shot.

Ah, the caramel bread pudding - now that's the real MVP! It's like eating a cloud made of sugar, spice, and everything nice. Karina's reheating tip was spot on - it's a dessert that keeps on giving.

A slight hiccup - the place was as barren of napkins as a desert, but a quick request later, and voila! Napkin oasis.

And don't forget to join their rewards program - who doesn't like being rewarded for treating themselves? Plus, they do custom cakes, because why not add more sweetness to life?

In summary, La Dolcekca is where your taste buds go on a mini-vacation. It's a charming spot with heart, flavor, and a dash of Dominican flair. Worth every penny and every minute(20 min) of the wait!
The chop cheese was so good! Staff was very friendly and answered all of my questions as a first timer.

Starting off, the location is easy to find and easy to park at. There was no wait when I visited (aside from waiting for my friends to join me). The owner greeted me and she was so nice and accommodating. The variety of pastries and food on the menu were great as I love to try new things. I ordered the fresh Mandarin Juice and Empanadas, 1 of each flavor (Ham & Cheese, Pulled Pork BBQ, Pepperoni Pizza, and Cheese). My friends ordered gourmet waffles with a side of eggs and the Salmon Chipotle sandwich with a side of fries. Everything was delicious. My friend got the Eggnog Tres Leches to go and I got the Strawberry Almond Cherry Cupcake for my MIL to go. I will definitely come back for more!

THIS PLACE!!!!!
My family and I travelled 1.5 hours specifically to try their chopped cheese sandwiches and desserts. We were not disappointed.
#1 The food and desserts are FIRE!!!!!  We're originally from NY, as is the owner, and let me tell you, their chopped cheese is the BEST I've ever had!!!!! PERIOD. Karina's (Owner) special touch on this sandwich is everything. They offer a wide array of desserts, and they are all fresh, tasty and moist. We got cupcakes, carrot cake, Tres Leches, and flan - all YUMMY!!!!
#2 The owner and staff are AMAZING!!!!! They explained the menu, answered all of our questions, made suggestions and offered excellent customer service.
#3 The amount of food you get for the price is the icing on the cake.
We will be back soon. It's well worth the trip!!!!!
Todo muy rico y el personal Demaciado amable
Delicious food! Baked goods were very tasty and the staff were very friendly! I had the salmon chipotle sandwich with the hibiscus natural juice drink and the chocolate filled vanilla cupcake.
La comida, el ambiente y el servicio es 100% recomendado.

Hoy visite la cafeteria  y me comi un delicioso sandwich de pollo con papitas a la Francesca y para cerrar con broche de oro me comi un helado de coco, asi es que se las recogiendo para que vengan a disfrutar de todo lo rico que venden por aca.
I was delighted by the atmosphere and warm greeting. The food was delicious.
Very good food and awesome pastries! I personally love the Ham & Cheese empanadas the best!

I had the pleasure of tasting the most delicious food at La Dolcekca Bakery Cafe. The sandwiches were amazing!! My kids loved the sweet treats of course. It was very nice and clean and everyone was very welcoming. I have visited La Dolcekca Bakery Cafe multiple times and will continue.

Everything was so fresh and hot! Literally the chicken empanada is the best I've had in Charlotte. Steak sandwich with fries was chef's kiss! The customer service was excellent, the place feels very homey which I really appreciated. I can't wait to go back to try some more things on the menu. Oh and the passion fruit juice, FIRE!!!

Very nice
I had the banana pudding and chicken empanadas. The owner was very nice the empanadas were fresh and very tasty.
Highly recommend.
The banana pudding was very good kinda pricy but its good. Saved me in a pinch for breakfast on Thanksgiving when everything was closed. I'm glad to support a small business like on a holiday.
The young Hispanic lady was so sweet and so helpful! The customer service and the food here is amazing. Thankyou sweetheart!
The empanadas were yummy and so filling! The staff was lovely and gave helpful recommendations. I adored the decorations and the overall vibe was cozy.
The front lady with the glasses made me the best sandwich today! So down to earth with positive energy! Will be back!
Such a cute place and the food was great. I had the French toast bites, scrambled eggs, and a cheese empanada. Would love to go back again.
Los mejore postres en charllote
Todo es delicioso

I ordered an empanada, the chimi sandwich combo, and the banana pudding (all were really good)! I loved how comforting both the food the restaurant were. I will definitely be back to try some more menu items with friends!

Everything we had was so tasty especially the chopped cheese and the enchiladas are ADDICTING . We literally went back three days later haha! You can tell all the food is made with high quality ingredients and love! Everyone working just makes it seem like you're visiting their home and they're making you the best food. The desserts are amazing so much to choose from. We felt so welcomed and taking care of. We will continue driving 30 minutes to visit, it's sooooo worth it!
good looking environment, with a lot of options and choices available. Definitely rockin with the spot

I really wanted to like everything about this place, but that just wasn't possible.

1-coffee- think it was instant-was charged extra for cream, and there was no refill available. Menu states price is $4, the bill stated $5.15. Extra milk-$1.50.
2- claimed the barely warm waffle was fresh made. It was not, I saw them place a premade waffle in some sort of panini press, to warm it.
3-one piece of bacon was all fat.

Service was slow. Overall just not great. Maybe other items are better. But, the waffle and bacon are not what you want.

The best chimi you will taste outside of DR or NYC
I think my sandwich was made with love because this sandwich was amazing. Compliments to the nice young lady who prepared it.

I decided to visit this bakery for the first time after seeing their sign from the parking lot near Bonchon. I was in the mood for some sweets so I stopped in. This is a cute little place and the decor is very nice and inviting. I ordered 2 cupcakes. The female employee was so wonderful and kind and tried her best to assist me. None of the cupcakes were labeled so I didn't know what I was ordering and had to rely on the employee to tell me what the flavors were and she didn't seem to know all of the flavors either since all you can see is the frosting. The actual cake portion of the cupcake is covered up by the cardboard wrapper.
I ordered a strawberry cupcake and another that she said was "chocolate". The one that she gave me was not chocolate, it was actually some type of spice cake. It was pretty good even though it wasn't what I wanted. The strawberry cake on the other hand was awful. It was hard as a rock and tasted like it may have been sitting in the display  case for days. For over $5 for each cupcake, I was pretty disappointed. I see that all of their positive reviews are about the food so I think I will just try the food next time.
The best service and food!

nah they taxing for a choppped cheese? 15$? 18 on door dash? you're bugging , this is ny deli food I get "inflation" but a deli would not charge you no more than 7 to maybe 9 for a hero, much less for a roll. and before anyone comes at me telling me this is " nc " , life in NY in general is more expensive. especially for business/ rent. residential and commercial. overall cost of living.

review of comment to response , it's a chopped cheese. it's foundation is ground beef which is dirt cheap and  cheese. chopped cheese was never meant to be a hippy luxury dish. it's comfort food , despite a chopped cheese being cheaper in nyc it will always beat what this over priced sandwich is.

I came in Frantic! Looking for a last minute wedding cake. The baker prior did not make what I requested. The owner took amazing care of me and even had props I could rent. Thanks to her my reception was saved! Side note the food is good as well!!
Thank you so much for the awesome coffee and pastry yesterday! Can't wait to stop by again soon!
Best lemon bar I've ever had
Loved this place!! Friendly stuff, amazing food! We will definitely come back!!
I love the chop cheese, the flan, the cake , coffees!!! Everything in this bakery including services is all top tier.

My husband and I got a Strawberry Tres Leches & Strawberry Cupcake to share. I love tres leches and it was cool how many different flavors they have.

I recently found out they have food (not just desserts), so I'd love to try that as well.
Tried their salmon chipotle today and it was amazing! Will be back
Great staff... Super friendly and the chop cheese is amazing. Definitely one of my go to spots.
Great friendly service. The owner was hands on and definitely going back again and again .The food is amazing and they have the best chopped cheese in the world.

Wish I could give one star! Ordered bakery items and spent a lot of money and they were out of something I ordered so I asked if I could replace it with something that was 2 more dollars and was told no even though I spent 65 dollars with them! I am still trying to get my little bit of money back from that item and when I have emailed the owner she says I'm making threats. I would never do that over something this small!!! But definitely won't be back! I have several more details to this story but I simply want to give my rating and my 8 dollars back from the 65 I spent, and everything tasted old in my opinion cinnamon roll was hard as a rock! But she says that's a threat
Please do yourself a favour and try this place out!!! The chop cheese sandwich is the truth. This is going to be my new spot!

The owner greeted me at the door with the warmest smile. We had a conversation and I felt like I was back in NY at home!! Listen, ask for a salmon chopped cheese with tamarind juice or soursop juice!!!! She knows what she is doing with hot Sammie's and pastries!!!! I got cheesecake flan (YES CHEESECAKE FLAN) and biscoff cheesecake!! EVERYTHING WAS 10'S across the board!! She's has a repeat customer here!! The presentation, service, & taste of everything is top tier!!

This spot is tucked in off of Montford Drive in Charlotte. It's almost like a Dominican Amelie's but smaller and better entrees. The food was flavorful. I had a chop cheese and Cajun pasta and an empanada. To drink I had mango juice. I was impressed with the portions. The service was amazing. The restaurant is small so be prepared to either take your food to go or position yourself for a good seat
Very nice staff and super cute place!

Fantastic. We found this place on a whim. It's a super cute cafe.  The menu is not expansive but it doesn't have to be. The food is PHENOMENAL!!!!!  The bakery selection is a great variety and everything we had was fantastic. I highly recommend La Dolcekca.
Great small restaurant/bakery with a lot of flavor. The Chop Cheese is up there as one of the best I've ever had. Very filling too.

The owner exudes love for her craft & customer's Cozy shop where you can even sit and enjoy your food or grab and go The pastries are fresh flaky some savory others sweet Empanadas fresh and hot Chop Cheese! I'm from NJ and seeing that took me back Delicious ice cream and Sorbet served to the right of the main dishes Everything made you smile and tasting the food kept the smile on Huge props to the owner she is amazing please try this place it's open 10-10
Delicioso
Deliciosa la comida y excelente atencion

Stumbled upon this place when craving desert.  I consider myself lucky to have discovered it.  Why did I not know about this place sooner?   Great service, excellent desert selections and delicious.  I ordered the chocoflan and enjoyed every bite.  Can't wait to go back and try their sandwiches and empanadas!
Beautiful spot for coffee break with sweets and great breakfast sandwiches.
great service from owner. loved learning about her story on line. also great pastry offering

I have had the choppsandwich, Carmel tres leche cake, chocolate cake and empanadas all were delicious. My favorites have been the savory items!  Get chopped sandwich if you have never been. It's huge, big enough to share or have left overs! Heats up great in the oven

I do not recommend this place. My boyfriend had ordered a cake to surprise me with, paid in full and order two weeks ahead of the scheduled date and time. He showed them a picture to confirm the design. However, when it was time to pick up the cake, they claimed it wasn't ready because they had forgotten about it. Instead of taking responsibility, the owner kept blaming him and caused a back-and-forth argument when she should have added it to her calendar. As a result to their forgetfulness, they rushed to make the cake, resulting in a final design that bore no resemblance to what he had initially shown them. To top it off, the cake filling they used was not the one he had requested.

The white hearted shaped cake is was was requested and the pink not even heart shaped was what the gave.
Beautiful interior, friendly staff and tasty food. What more could one ask for!!
My new favorite place to eat. Great food and great family owned restaurant.
El mejor banana puding
Muy rico los tres leches
Lo mejor
Best Cuban sandwich I've had in a long while. Croquettes were to die for. And service was excellent.
Cookies great, mini cakes muh
This is place is great! The food is fantastic and the service is amazing! Best desserts in Charlotte!!
los mejores pasteles
Los mejores pasteles
El mejor tres leches de Charlotee
Los mejores pasteles de chocolate!
The best place for eat pancakes!!
Their empanadas are mind blowingly delicious. We ordered two and decided it was a mistake to not order one of every flavor.

What a fantastic place that I came across!! This is a Bakery and restaurant that serves unbelievable  authentic delicacies...The owner is one of the nicest people I have ever met and her daughter does some of the baking!!! Really strong coffee for sure!!! This is a true "Gem" not to be missed
The sandwiches are a little pricy but it tastes great. Their tres leches (in multiple flavors) are great
Great Fresh Food! Great Service and Great Vibes
Best breakfast place in Charleston!
Great tasty desserts, & an authentic tasting Tamarind drink!!!!

I went here for the first time today. I found it both awkward and difficult to eat here. There is no drink menu, no trash can, and no place to get utensils from. We only got sweets. I wasn't super impressed by any of them. But I would make mention that the owner and her employees are all very nice.

The owner has very good taste to decorte. I will give them 3 stars for that and because customer service was great.   It was pricy and we were not impressed with what we had:  A cookie, a bread pudding, 1 cold brew coffee and 1 juice including 15% tip. $30. Neither of us liked the desserts or the drinks.
The owner is amazing!! Good dessert and coffee
Everything is delicious. Get there early as they sell FAST. Recommend: any cheesecake is PHENOMENAL and the stuffed churros are fried when you order. 5+ Stars
It is in the bldg beside Jeff's Bucket Shop. Amazing pastries & empanadas! Great customer service!!  I highly recommend!!
Cute aesthetic. Highly highly recommend the chop cheese
This is the BEST bakery in South charlotte. I love the desserts and the Food!!..Everything here is amazing.. I highly recommend
Los sandwich mas deliciosos del mundo mundial los ame definitivamente mi lugar favorito y los jugos exquisitos ame
Me encanto la Bakery Cafe los Tres leches estan sabrosos!! Tienen que venir a probarlos!!
Very cute Bakery. They have a lot of desert options and seem to offer a variety of empanadas.
Omgosh my family and I went last week and I was salivating sweets was yummy!! Next week I'll try breakfast !!!

Awww, I love how this place was decorated throughout in a Paris theme highlight in pink. Perfect spot to have a nice tea date with lots of baked sweets and some food options. The empanadas are definitely I must when you come filled and packed with flavor. They are cooked to order. I also enjoyed the pineapple cupcake it had a nice glaze on top and on the bottom of the cupcake. The lady working was really nice and offered us a sa while she cooked our empanadas. No worries there are plenty of parking  spaces.
Best tres leches ever! Her juices are homemade and soooo good. The owner is so sweet and she makes the most beautiful and yummy cakes!

Loved everything about this Cafe!
The decor is beautiful, the owner is super nice and the food is delicious!!

I really love this place   it feels like home, the coffee the empanadas the dessert are just delicious  I love how the owner make you feel welcome, 100% recommended, come with your friends and your love ones and you will have a great time.

If I could give zero stars I would. Everything I got was absolutely terrible!!! No flavor and SOGGY!!!!  It literally was like someone poured lots of water in all the cake. I had to pour out the liquid to taste it. I will not be returning. Worst bakery I've ever experienced.
We purchased cake pops for a baby shower and they were perfect! Great size and very delicious. So many compliments from our guests. Definitely will be visiting this lovely bakery again soon!

3 month follow up!!!!!  Service and food were wonderful!  I dined in this time and it felt like I was visiting a relative.  I can't wait til my next visit!

Very nice!  Great service, hot & delicious food.  I called in my order, gave my estimated arrival and it was hot off the grill!  Everyone was nice and friendly, I look forward to my next visit for cheesecake!
